This paper deals with image alignment using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of self-supervised learning, which is a popular area of research in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the use of convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses images from electron microscopy, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
